This paper deals with the problem of cell discovery in millimeter wave cellular networks, which involves the use of directional beamforming for communication. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves simulations based on experimental measurements, which suggests that it may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) or Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with the design and optimization of cellular networks, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computer Communications (cs.COM) sub-category.
